title: How are the phone ROM and RAM allocated?
answer:
The ROM and RAM sizes displayed on your phone may be smaller than the values in the phone specifications, because the system occupies a part. 

 4 GB ROM 

 The ROM contains system applications, files, and databases, which takes up about 1.5 GB. The ROM space available to users is 2.5 GB. You can use this 2.5 GB space to store any types of files.
